The bar shows $\frac{2}{3}$ shaded.
[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]
\fill[gray!40] (0,0) rectangle (4,1.2);
\draw (0,0) rectangle (6,1.2);
\draw (2,0)--(2,1.2);
\draw (4,0)--(4,1.2);
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]
Split each third into $2$ equal parts. What equivalent fraction is now shaded?
